What is Pain Management Information System?
The Pain Management Information System (PMIS) serves as a unified hub for capturing pain scores, medication regimens, procedural notes, and patient‑reported outcomes. It links directly with enterprise EHRs, pharmacy systems, and billing engines, ensuring that every data point is available to clinicians at the point of care. By providing real‑time dashboards, trend visualizations, and alerts for out‑of‑range values, PMIS empowers clinicians to adjust analgesic strategies promptly, thereby mitigating the risk of chronic pain escalation and opioid misuse.
